metadata.title: Multichannel Seismic-Reflection Profiles Aleutian Arc and Trench, Alaska USGS Open File Reports 88-502 and 89-202

creators.name: Atmospheric Administration (NOAA), National Environmental Satellite, Data
Information Service (NESDIS), National Geophysical Data Center (NGDC)

metadata.description:
In June and July 1980 and again in July and August 1981, the
U.S. Geological Survey (USGS) conducted reconnaissance surveys
from 171 degrees W to 173 degrees E longitude along the Aleutian
Arc and Trench near the islands of Atka, Amlia, Kiska, Agattu and
Seguam.  A total of 2880 km of 24-channel seismic-reflection data
were collected on the USGS Research Vessel S.P. Lee (USGS cruise
identifiers L5-80-AA and L9-81-AA).  These profiles are now
available for purchase from the National Geophysical Data Center
(NGDC).
